having at least 5 years’ practical experience in the field of the recognition, obtained within the 7 years preceding the application for recognition</li></ul></li><li>having successfully completed a <strong>training course</strong> in which the subjects listed in <a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=36635&amp;woLang=nl\">annex 9 of the VLAREL</a> are covered.</li></ul></li></ul><h2>Validity period and obligations</h2><p>The recognition is valid for an <strong>indefinite period</strong>. As a recognised ‘environmental expert in noise and vibrations’, you must meet the following obligations among others to retain your recognition:</p><ul><li>each year, undergo <strong>refresher training</strong> of at least 8 hours on the most recent developments and legislation on noise and vibrations for which you are recognised (noise and/or vibrations)</li><li>hold <strong>insurance</strong> for third-party liability, including professional liability, in connection with the use of the recognition</li><li>pay the<a href=\"https://www.uat-vlaanderen.be/vlarel-retributies\"> annual fee</a>. The first payment is to be made in the year following the year in which you obtained the recognition. Failure to pay the annual fee will lead to automatic suspension of the recognition following a formal notice of default. If the fee is not paid within 30 days of the suspension, the recognition will automatically lapse.</li></ul><p><a href=\"https://omgeving.vlaanderen.be/informatie-voor-erkende-milieudeskundigen-bodemcorrosie\">More info on the obligations for recognised environmental experts</a> can be found on the Department of Environment and Spatial Development website.</p>","nl-BE-x-generated-informal":"<p>Om erkend te worden als ‘milieudeskundige geluid en trillingen’, moet je voldoen aan:</p><ul><li><a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=36058\">algemene erkenningsvoorwaarden</a> die gelden voor alle erkenningen leefmilieu:<ul><li>in de 3 jaar 